ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: How much do your child's problems affect how he or she gets along with other children?
Notes: 0= No Problem, Does Not Need Treatment; 6= Extreme Problem, Needs Treatment

ElementDescription: How much do your child's problems affect how he or she gets along with brothers or sisters? (Option to indicate if child does not have siblings)
Notes: 0= No Problem, Does Not Need Treatment; 6= Extreme Problem, Needs Treatment; 999= No Applicable

ElementDescription: How much do your child's problems affect his or her relationship with you (and your partner, if present)?
Notes: 0= No Problem, Does Not Need Treatment; 6= Extreme Problem, Needs Treatment

ElementDescription: How much do your child's problems affect your family in general?
Notes: 0= No Problem, Does Not Need Treatment; 6= Extreme Problem, Needs Treatment

ElementDescription: How much do your child's problems affect him or her in general?
Notes: 0= No Problem, Does Not Need Treatment; 6= Extreme Problem, Needs Treatment

ElementDescription: Please rate the overall severity of your child's mood or behavior problems and need for treatment.
Notes: 0= No Problem, Does Not Need Treatment; 6= Extreme Problem, Needs Treatment

ElementDescription: (Behavior) Cooperation Subscale Score
Notes: Sum of items irsa_b_behav01 to irsa_b_behav17

ElementDescription: (Behavior) Self-Control/Self-Regulation Subscale Score

ElementDescription: (Behavior) Total Score
Notes: Sum of items irsa_b_behav01 to irsa_b_behav39
